    "Moreover, there is mounting evidence (Alderson-Day and Fernyhough, 2015; Fernyhough and Borghi, 2023) that such process of cognitive development is accompanied by the evolution of inner or covert speech that associates a symbolic component to the maturation of subsymbolic sensorimotor capabilities.",
    "Such linguistic component has also been linked to the role of inner speech in working memory (Miyake and Shah, 1999), namely the retention of information \"online, \" critical for a complex task."
